This ode has been animadverted upon pretty severely, and even rejected as spurious, because unequal to the occasion it was written for. It may'not be one of Horace’s best. But it was evidently only a private affair. It was composed at the close of the Canta- brian war, A.tJ.c. 729, when Augustus' return was expected, or on his return the follow- ing year. He was detained by illness at Tarracona.
